abstract: Tehran uses religious arguments, anti-imperialist nationalism and neo-Stalinist repression to ensure compliance.
snippet: Tehran uses religious arguments, anti-imperialist nationalism and neo-Stalinist repression to ensure compliance.
lead_paragraph: Historians will record the blood-soaked days of November as some of the worst mass killings of protesters in modern Iranian history. A sudden increase in fuel prices led to protests across the country; the regime responded with brute violence.

abstract: President Trump is trying to use his administration’s assault on transgender rights to put Democrats in a bind.
snippet: President Trump is trying to use his administration’s assault on transgender rights to put Democrats in a bind.
lead_paragraph: If you’re a Democratic strategist, what do you do to reconcile the moral power of your party’s arguments about the inherent dignity and civil rights of every American with the reality of an electorate that has not caught up with where the party has gone and is slightly — or more than slightly — averse to it? How do you decide whether what is right is also what is wise?

headline_main: Are There Limits to the Rights Revolution?

abstract: Americans deserve a stronger assurance than “hope” that their Fourth Amendment rights are being respected.
snippet: Americans deserve a stronger assurance than “hope” that their Fourth Amendment rights are being respected.
lead_paragraph: The F.B.I.’s investigation of the former Trump campaign adviser Carter Page, we can now say with assurance, was a train wreck. In his report, Justice Department Inspector General Michael Horowitz cataloged a damning list of egregious errors, omissions or misrepresentations in filings to the secretive Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Court, which approved nearly a year’s worth of wiretaps on Mr. Page.

abstract: A Southern California native went looking for an old-fashioned Christmas. She found it in the “Christmas ornament town” of Seiffen, tucked in Germany’s Ore Mountains.
snippet: A Southern California native went looking for an old-fashioned Christmas. She found it in the “Christmas ornament town” of Seiffen, tucked in Germany’s Ore Mountains.
lead_paragraph: For as long as I can remember, I’ve had this image of Christmas: a village nestled in a snowy valley, candlelit windows glowing against a night sky. I’m not sure where it came from. Growing up in sunny Southern California, my family strung lights on the palm trees in our yard and went to the beach on Christmas Eve. Most kids know about Santa’s sleigh, but I believed he traveled on a magic speedboat.

abstract: With her play and her talk, did the soccer star inspire us to redefine the meaning of sports? She tried.
snippet: With her play and her talk, did the soccer star inspire us to redefine the meaning of sports? She tried.
lead_paragraph: Of all the brilliant fireworks of the 2019 sports season, the color purple — and the woman who wore it — defined the year.
